The Telegraph - Calcutta

 SAF Games put off

Colombo: The 10th South Asian Games, scheduled to be hosted by Sri Lanka in August, has been postponed by a year in the wake of the tsunami disaster. 

Lanka minister of youth affairs and sports Jeewan Kumaratunga said the Games, previously called South Asian Federation (SAF) Games, were being postponed as the time was not ripe to host such an event. 

Besides Sri Lanka and powerhouses India, the regional Games is participated by Pakistan, Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Nepal, Bhutan and the Maldives. 

The last edition of the Games was held in Islamabad after it was postponed thrice. 

That postponement, though was due to the political condition of the regions. This time the Games are postponed because of a natural disaster. 

